<output>
<analysis>
<has-cmf>False. There is no CMF number present in the provided post information.</has-cmf>
<refers-to-candidate>False. The post does not refer to any specific parliamentary candidate by name, surname, or party affiliation.  The text "Ar vota pentru dreapta democratică!" (I would vote for the democratic right) is a general statement and doesn't identify a particular candidate or party from the provided list.</refers-to-candidate>
<addresses-the-wide-population>True.  The post is a paid advertisement on Facebook, a public platform, and therefore addresses a wide population. The image and text are not directed at a specific individual.</addresses-the-wide-population>
<electoral-objective>False. While the post encourages voting ("Hai la vot!" - Let's vote!), it does not advocate for or against any specific candidate or party. The statement about voting for the "democratic right" is too general to be considered direct electoral propaganda. The image of kittens is unrelated to any political party or candidate.</electoral-objective>
<journalism>False. The post is not journalistic in nature. It lacks any news, analysis, or opinion pieces on political events. It's a simple encouragement to vote, with a vague preference for the "democratic right," presented in a lighthearted manner.</journalism>
<personal_opinion>True. The post can be interpreted as expressing a personal opinion about the importance of voting and a general preference for a right-leaning democratic party. However, this opinion is not presented in a way that directly influences the vote for a specific candidate or party.</personal_opinion>
</analysis>

<conclusion>
<post_id>1263155711687281</post_id>
<electoral-propaganda-analysis>
The Facebook post, while mentioning voting and expressing a general political preference, lacks the specific elements required to constitute electoral propaganda under Article 98 t) of LEGE nr. 208 din 20 iulie 2015.  It does not identify any specific candidate or party, and its overall tone is not persuasive or coercive. The image is unrelated to any political campaign.  The general call to vote is not prohibited.  The statement "Ar vota pentru dreapta democratică!" is a personal opinion, not a call to action for a specific candidate.
</electoral-propaganda-analysis>
<electoral-propaganda-decision>FALSE</electoral-propaganda-decision>
